- Polyarchy refers to a form of government where power is distributed among multiple centers, reflecting democratic principles;
- Civil liberties encompass the rights and freedoms of individuals protected by laws and constitutions;
- The overall rank is calculated by averaging the ranks from the media freedom index, polyarchy level, and civil liberties index.
